pageContext.description: Well patinated; square socket, prominent collar; reeds very slender, prominent internal ridges on two faces.
pageContext.associations: Part of Keadby Hoard found in bed of river trent at considerable depth; accounts vary as to size of hoard and depth found. Donor said this was one of ten and found at a depth of 10 feet. (See also Scunthorpe Museum B.21).
